def: The act of besieging, or the state of being besieged. Golding.
To release, as one thing stuck to another. Richardson.

One of a Teutonic race, formerly dwelling on the south shore ofthe Baltic, the most barbarous and fierce of the northern nationsthat plundered Rome in the 5th century, notorious for destroying themonuments of art and literature.
The act of drawing after, or pursuing, deer with a dog. Cowell.
Evidence; declaration. [Obs.]The sensible and true avouch Of mine own eyes. Shak.
A knife or short dagger, esp. that in use among the Highlandersof Scotland. [Variously spelt.] "His skean, or pistol." Spenser.
The state or quality of being puissant; puissance; power.
